!! Hamilton's Rule
Altruism evolves when the cost to the actor is outweighed by the benefit to the relative, weighted by their genetic relatedness:

//rB > C//

!! Coefficients of Relatedness (r)
* '''0.5 (50%):''' Parents to Children, Full Siblings.
* '''0.25 (25%):''' Grandparents/Grandchildren, Aunts/Uncles, Nieces/Nephews.
* '''0.125 (12.5%):''' First Cousins.

!! Haplodiploidy
In ants and bees, the unique sex-determination system makes sisters share 75% of their genes (r=0.75), explaining why workers often forgo their own reproduction to raise sisters.